  • vector
)
Spinor3 chainable

Defined in src/davinci-eight/math/Spinor3.ts:173

this ⟼ dual(this)

Sets this Spinor to the value of the dual of the vector, I * v. Notice that the dual of a vector is related to the spinor by the right-hand rule.

Parameters:

  • vector Cartesian3

    The vector whose dual will be used to set this spinor.

Defined in src/davinci-eight/math/Spinor3.ts:385

Sets this Spinor to the value of its reflection in the plane orthogonal to n. The geometric formula for bivector reflection is B' = n * B * n.
